:: action-drive-to-lancaster-farm
You leave the abandoned police station and drive south to [[County Road 66->loc-county-road-6]].

You wonder if it's a holiday because you haven't seen anyone or any moving cars. You have passed houses, mostly in need of repair, but no signos of life. Perhaps there is a local festival or some other event that has drawn all the people.

You pass a video store, sitting alone in an empty, damaged parking lot. The store window is dark.

You approach a church but it too seems deserted, the parking lot empty and the doors closed.
There is a sign near the road that reads:
Ephrata Church of the Brethen
Take the Lenten Pledge

Lenten? You think to yourself. You recall something about lent being a religious observance before Easter where people give up something they like for a period of time. You wonder what people in this town might give up.

You turn east on County Road 66 and you approach what must be the [[Lancaster Farm->loc-lancaster-farm]].

You pull into the driveway. You note a few cars but you don't see anyone, not even a barking dog coming to greet you. It is late afternoon but there is still enough light that you can't tell if any lights are on in the house or if it too is abandoned.

There is a large porch that extends from the front door across the front of the house before wrapping around the West side of the house and extending to the North side.

You exit your vehicle, take one last look around and then [[step onto the large wraparound porch.->action-start-chapter-porch]]

:: action-start-chapter-porch 
<<set $chapter to "porch">>

The front door is wooden, old and blemished with a circular window, large enough to frame a face, set near the top. You knock and wait.

No response.

You listen for a moment. There is no responding sound from inside the house, just the wind in the trees.

You knock on the door a second time as you try to peer into the house through the small window. But it is dark within and you only see your own reflection. But this time you hear [[something->object-sound-of-a-polaroid-camera]].

You step back, confused. More determined now, you step forward and pound on the door and clearly and loudly announce yourself.

<<you>>Pennsylvania State Trooper! Police! Anyone home? Please respond!<</you>>

It is as the door stops resonating from your knock that you hear a new sound. Louder - like a screen door slamming shut. A side door?

You walk quickly along the porch and turn the corner. You can see there is another door at the end of the porch and it seems to be ajar. But more importantly, you see a figure running away, disappearing around the Northwest corner of the house.

This triggers your instincts and you leap into [[pursuit->action-pursuit-1]].

:: action-pursuit-1

You race to the end of the porch and jump off the steps into what must be the backyard. There is a pool in the center of the yard and you are forced to run around it, past the rusted chain link fence that enloses it and past a single story building along the far side of the pool. With the fence on the left and the forest on the other side and in front, there seems no where else to go - but you see a gap in the brush and you enter and find yourself on a path in the woods.
<<you>>Stop! Police!<</you>>

You try again to get the figure to stop as you continue your pursuit. The path leads eastward and you think you can hear something pushing through the brush but it's difficult to be sure because you own motions are making noise as well.
Branches claw at your body as you [[run->action-pursuit-2]]

:: action-pursuit-2
Soon, the path opens up into a small clearing. You see a barn, a shed and a gravel road that heads back South.  In back of these strucutres are some sort of crop. Your hunch is that the figure either entered the shed, the barn or it is escaping back toward the road. 

Your first bet is the shed, but the door is metal and is closed - you would have heard that door close if anyone entered. You decide to enter the barn as the door is open and stop 10 feet into the building. You are surrounded by hay bales and farming equipment. You look around but don't see anyone and you don't hear anything. 

Regretfully, you conclude that the mysterious figure must have slipped away back toward the road. You are tired but jog out of the barn and gallop [[toward the main road.->action-pursuit-3]]

:: action-pursuit-3

The dirt road is narrow and flanked by tall crops on either side. You push forward, your footsteps accentuate by the gravel beneath you. Looking ahead, you are sure this dirt road will end on the main road, County Road 66, and you are correct. You see what must be the Lancaster's mailbox near their driveway.

A check along the main road shows no sign of the mysterious figure. You can see the Lancaster driveway from here - your patrol vehicle is where you left it and there is no sign of any other vehicles in motion.
With no other option you [[return to the house.->action-pursuit-4]]

:: action-pursuit-4
You quickly climb the front stairs onto the porch walk briskly along it and along the side until you have returned to where you first saw the mysterious figure.
You approach the side door and find that the screen door is ajar as it was before, but now you can see that the door, also, is not fully closed. You feel justified to enter the house.

[[You announce yourself and push into the house->action-enter-kitchen]]

:: action-enter-kitchen
<<set $chapter to "bernadette">>\
You are in, what appears to be, the kitchen of the Lancaster house. There are some appliances straight in front of you and a counter to your right.
To your surprise, there is a [[woman->character-bernadette]] standing on the other side of a short kitchen counter. She looks up, surprised as well.
<<bern>>Well, hello there...officer?<</bern>>
You breathe a sigh of relief and introduce yourself and the reason for your visit. The woman introduces herself as Bernadette, a neighbor who was just checking on the family as she has not seen them in church that day. 
Bernadette has short, brunette hair and pale skin, probably in her mid-40s you would guess and has a sturdy, even athletic build, one you would expect from someone who works the land. She is even wearing a pair of gardening gloves. 
<<you>>I saw someone in the back yard and they ran off when they saw me. Did you see anyone? Would you know who that was?<</you>>
<<bern>>No. No, I didn't see anyone - no idea on who that could have been if it weren't one of the Lancasters. I walked up the main road and straight to the side door - I always use the side door.<</bern>>
<<you>>Any idea where the Lancasters might be today?<</you>>
<<bern>>Oh, if they aren't here, they must be somewhere related to a church activity; they are very active...but it was strange not seeing them today. It does seem they are involved in the obervance of Lent.<</bern>>
<<you>>Lent?<</you>>
You walk closer to the counter and now you can see there are various documents and announcements related to the church and Lent.
<<bern>>Yes, officer, it's a Christian observance. You are not familiar? You never gave up something for Lent?<</bern>>

You ignore the question, feeling the conversation is veering off course.
<<you>>I apologize Ma'am, I'm trying to determine if I should be concerned about the well-being of this family. You said you didn't seem them today, but you expect they might be at church? Is there any number I could call?<</you>>

She looks at you sympathetically.
<<bern>>I'm sorry, I don't have any information I can give to you. These bulletins probably have some contact information that you could use to reach the pastor or the church office? I would start there. If I think of anything else, I'll let you know.<</bern>>

You nod and pull one of the [[documents->object-lent-documents]] to you.


When you look up again, the woman is gone.
<<addinventory "??card??" "card-the-samaritan">>\
You do find some phone numbers within the various documents, but no one answers any of your calls.
You decide it is time to search the property for a member of the family or any hint as to where they may be. 
